Head of Department of Free State Department of Agriculture and Rural Development, Peter Thabethe,  is set to testify at the state capture inquiry on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - The Judicial Commission of Inquiry into allegations of State Capture, Corruption and Fraud in the Public Sector including Organs of State resumed on Tuesday. Senior Hawks investigator, Kobus Roelofse, has taken to the stand at the state capture inquiry. He investigated former Crime Intelligence head, Richard Mdluli. WATCH: SABC still in the spotlight at state capture inquiry On Monday, the testimony of the former head of the Free State Department of Agriculture, Peter Thabethe, was postponed due to the withdrawal of his legal team. This year marks one year since the commission was established.